<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-17-0592 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Bangladesh government is preparing to launch a major reorganisationof the country's rapidly expanding natural gas sector. Proposals nowunder consideration are aimed at restructuring the organisation of upstreamand downstream activities under the umbrella of state-owned BangladeshOil, Gas and Minerals Corporation (BOGMC), which is responsible for thenation's entire gas industry with the exception of LPG bottling and retailsales. Moves to improve the operating efficiency of the gas sector arebeing timed to coincide with two major World Bank and Asian DevelopmentBank-backed projects. These will help boost gas production, transmissionand utilisation in the northern and central regions of Bangladesh's EasternZone where most gas reserves lie.</TEXT></DOC>